The paper discusses energy efficiency in wireless communication networks, which falls under the category of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The approach used in the paper is based on game theory, which suggests that it could also be classified under the sub-category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also mentions the use of evolutionary biology as inspiration for the approach, which could classify it under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of local rules and fitness evaluation, which could classify it under the sub-categories of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and information theory (cs.IT).
